{"type":"message","id":"fea99437","parentId":"8ecd7992","timestamp":"2026-02-15T11:06:16.462Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sun 2026-02-15 13:06 GMT+2] OBSERVABILITY: SELF-INTEGRATION & DASHBOARD (Pro Stream).\n\n1.  **Self-Integration (LangFuse):**\n    *   *Concept:* Wrap my own `agent_loop` or key functions (`generate_code`, `analyze_error`) with `@observe()` decorator from `langfuse`.\n    *   *Action:* Since I cannot modify my own binary runtime, I will create a **Python Wrapper Script** (`src/agent_wrapper.py`) that imports `dmarket_api` and `trade_logic` and runs them with LangFuse tracing enabled. This allows me to \"see\" the bot's logic execution trace.\n\n2.  **Deep Scan (`D:\\Dmarket_bot`):**\n    *   Use `pyreverse` (if available via `pylint`) or static analysis to map: `TelegramUpdate -> BotHandler -> TradeManager -> DMarketClient (Ed25519)`.\n    *   *Goal:* Identify the exact flow of data.\n\n3.  **Update `SYSTEM_FLOW.md`:**\n    *   Add detailed Mermaid Sequence Diagram:\n        *   `User` -> `Telegram` -> `Bot` -> `TradeManager` (Check Redis Cache) -> `FlashValidator` (If Code Change) -> `DMarketAPI` (Sign Request) -> `Redis` (Store Result).\n\n4.  **Streamlit Dashboard (Prototype):**\n    *   Create `D:\\Dmarket_bot\\src\\dashboard\\app.py`.\n    *   *Features:*\n        *   **Sidebar:** Bot Status (Running/Stopped).\n        *   **Main:** \"Thinking Activity\" (Tail `logs/bot.log`), \"Project Files\" (Tree view of `src/`).\n    *   *Launch:* `streamlit run src/dashboard/app.py --server.headless true`.\n\n5.  **Output:**\n    *   Confirmation of `agent_wrapper.py` (Trace enabled).\n    *   Updated `SYSTEM_FLOW.md` content.\n    *   Streamlit app URL (local).\n    *   Text description of the \"Critical Chain\"."}],"timestamp":1771153576460}}
